# Keep the deployment lean and the scoring core / research OFF Vercel.
# (Vercel serves only the built `dist/` anyway — these are never web-served —
#  but excluding them keeps the upload small and the core source off the host.)
# api/ excluded ON PURPOSE: the backend runs on Railway now (all /api routes) and
# vercel.json rewrites /api/* there. If these functions deployed, Vercel's
# filesystem match would shadow the rewrite. They stay in the repo as a fallback.
api/
scripts/
docs/
supabase/
Progress/
packages/scoring/tests/
README.md
cspell.json
*.log
.env*
!.env.example
